ave tried to adjust both the down force and the.";i:13;s:46:"My garage door starts to close and then opens.";i:14;s:58:"A garage door that closes then opens is a serious concern.";i:15;s:109:"It can take up time as you try to solve the problem and it can be inconvenient as well as a security concern.";i:16;s:57:"Reasons Why Your Garage Door Keeps Opening After Closing.";i:17;s:96:"If your garage door keeps going back up after youve closed it the most common reason is because.";i:18;s:70:"Yes its possible although rare for your garage door to open by itself.";i:19;s:72:"There are a few unusual factors that can cause your door open by itself.";i:20;s:42:"Here are a few scenarios weve come across.";i:21;s:144:"Residential electric garage door openers manufactured after 1993 are equipped with two safety mechanisms that operate while the door is closing.";i:22;s:56:"The first is photoelectric and the second is mechanical.";i:23;s:140:"Thunderstorms and windstorms can cause power outages and surges that may damage the electrical circuits that open and close the garage door.";i:24;s:60:"This damage can cause the door to open and close on its own.";i:25;s:144:"If you suspect there is a problem with your circuit board you will want to contact a professional garage door repairman to diagnose the problem.";i:26;s:36:"You may need to have an electrician.";i:27;s:156:"How to fix the garage door when it opens by itselfSuddenly my garage door was opening on its own at least couple times a day it starter when i tried to set.";i:28;s:157:"It can be unnerving to hear your garage door opener run when no ones coming home or to find the garage door unexpectedly open in the morning or after a trip.";i:29;s:166:"When an automatic garage door opener opens and closes the door on its own its called phantom operation Fortunately the causes and solutions are usually fairly simple.";i:30;s:121:"In most cases where your garage door is open or close by itself is the cause for your opener having a faulty logic board.";i:31;s:60:"The logic board or Circuit board is the brain of the opener.";i:32;s:89:"A faulty board will in most scenarios sometime cause the door to open or close by itself.";i:33;s:77:"Your garage door is programmed to travel a certain distance before it closes.";i:34;s:138:"If it closes before that distance has been traveled it thinks something is wrong and it reopens to help prevent any damage or safety risk.";i:35;s:62:"But changes in weather conditions can causes your garage door.";i:36;s:39:"The garage door goes down then back up.";i:37;s:49:"Your garage door opens immediately after closing.";i:38;s:40:"The garage door keeps going up and down.";i:39;s:47:"Your garage door opens when it hits the ground.";i:40;s:39:"Garage door opener keeps going back up.";i:41;s:34:"It may be your garage door sensor.";i:42;s:101:"There are four common problems with garage door sensors three of these homeowners can fix themselves.";i:43;s:196:"The concept behind a garage door opener is that one press of a button will open and close the door helping reduce the stress strain and otherwise inconvenient task of manually performing this job.";i:44;s:138:"However there can be seemingly odd instances in which a door will open on its own without any interaction from the owner of the structure.";i:45;s:95:"Below are three reasons why your garage door opens on its own and some quick fixes you can try.";i:46;s:53:"Garage doors use radio frequencies to open and close.";i:47;s:160:"Whether youre using the passcode entry the buttons inside the garage or your remote opener the openers and the garage door itself must be on the same frequency.";i:48;s:83:"A garage door that opens or shuts on its own is not a random act that just happens.";i:49;s:62:"Instead there is a reason and a purpose that can be explained.";i:50;s:83:"One of the first potential causes for such a problem pertains to the circuit board.";i:51;s:101:"A garage door that randomly opens by itself is not a common problem but does occur from time to time.";i:52;s:161:"Garage door openers operate on one of many frequencies and while it is possible for one of your neighbors remotes to open your garage door it is highly unlikely.";i:53;s:86:"Newer openers operate on rolling codes making it almost impossible for this to happen.";i:54;s:168:"The remedy is as KennethR did clear all devices from your garage door by holding the learn button for 30 seconds -and reprogram all of your openers to your garage door.";i:55;s:86:"And check that no neighbors are opening their doors when your programming you openers.";}}